lf you haven't got a ha'penny, God bless you.

15
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,915
Straight from London.

16
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:14,957
(Thunder and crack of lightning)

17
00:03:46,625 --> 00:03:48,832
Good evening, miss.

18
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,415
l'm offering entertainment.

19
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:53,540
A show for the family.

20
00:03:53,708 --> 00:03:56,999
Comical pictures
of every description in colour.

21
00:03:57,166 --> 00:03:59,249
See.

22
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:04,957
Endless rollicking laughter.

23
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,415
Tell your master.

24
00:04:15,791 --> 00:04:17,874
l can ask.

25
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,915
(Dog barking)

26
00:05:57,041 --> 00:06:01,499
Roll up for the lantern show!
Only a penny!

27
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:05,915
You pay for the entertainment
but all the news is free!

28
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:09,707
North, east, west, south!

29
00:06:09,875 --> 00:06:12,332
All the news is free!

30
00:06:30,916 --> 00:06:32,999
(Tambourine rattling)

31
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:47,332
(Rattles and strikes tambourine)

32
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:13,790
(Violent striking of tambourine)

33
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:22,874
(Birdsong)

34
00:07:52,041 --> 00:07:54,124
Morning, Jacob.

35
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:01,707
Who's this? Oh! l can see.

36
00:08:01,875 --> 00:08:04,249
Who's this? l've seen that face somewhere.

37
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:07,790
l've seen that before. Who can it be, eh?
Who can it be?

38
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:10,624
You don't think l'm gonna drop you, do you?

39
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:12,749
Here we go, then.

40
00:08:12,916 --> 00:08:14,665
Way-ee-ee.

41
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:16,790
Off you go, then.

42
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:19,540
Be coming just over in a moment. Bye-bye.

43
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,790
Bye.

44
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:23,957
(Laughs)

45
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:26,957
The rascal.

46
00:08:30,791 --> 00:08:32,874
Children become you.

47
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:47,665
When can we have one of our own?

48
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,582
How can we manage?

49
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:55,707
Hm?

50
00:08:55,875 --> 00:08:57,957
l know times are hard.

51
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:05,207
But l'm not getting any younger.

52
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:15,290
We are the most beautiful people
in the whole world.

53
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:21,624
lt's true.

54
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:29,457
Good morning, family. Good morning.

55
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:31,332
Good morning.

56
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,582
(Laughter in background)

57
00:09:44,958 --> 00:09:46,415
Oh!

58
00:09:46,583 --> 00:09:47,915
Ooh.

59
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:50,165
(Laughter)

60
00:09:51,666 --> 00:09:53,749
WOMAN: Serves you right.

61
00:10:03,083 --> 00:10:05,957
And he went off and got himself a rabbit.

62
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:09,999
And he brought it back and he ate it.

63
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:11,915
And that's it.

64
00:10:12,083 --> 00:10:13,582
(Man chuckles)

65
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:18,457
WOMAN: Do you know, when l was younger,
l always had to sit between those two.

66
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:20,707
Nothing changes.

67
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:31,665
Let us say grace.

68
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:34,832
Dear Lord,

69
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:41,165
we humbly beseech thee to accept our gratitude
for this our daily bread.

70
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:46,874
Give us the goodness of heart to share
whatever we have.

71
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:49,874
Amen.

72
00:10:52,625 --> 00:10:54,707
VlCAR: Proverbs 14.

73
00:10:55,791 --> 00:10:58,790
ln all labour there is profit.

74
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:04,374
But the talk of the lips tendeth only to penury.

75
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:08,749
The poor is hated even of his own neighbour.

76
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:13,582
But the rich have many friends.

77
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:18,249
But in all labour there is profit.

78
00:11:19,166 --> 00:11:23,415
And it beho?es us to accept our lot in life

79
00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:27,207
and to work for our reward.

80
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:34,499
Let us never forget that our Lord
humbled himself for all our sakes

81
00:11:34,666 --> 00:11:37,582
to be born of the wife of a carpenter

82
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,832
on this poor earth.

83
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:45,915
Let us strive to excel in the role we are born to,

84
00:11:46,083 --> 00:11:52,374
remembering...
we are all beholden to our maker!

85
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:55,457
God the Father...

86
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:59,165
..in his infinite wisdom,

87
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,749
created large men and small,

88
00:12:01,916 --> 00:12:04,165
white men and black,

89
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,749
rich men and poor,

90
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:07,707
wise men...

91
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:10,415
..and fools.

92
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:18,665
And we shall not dare to presume
to question his wisdom!

93
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:24,915
Hold fast to that which we know
and have learned to value -

94
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:32,165
the natural order of things,
tried and tested down the ages of man.

95
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:41,499
lt is hardly a chance that in all living things
there is law and order.

96
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:45,874
There are enemies of the Church,

97
00:12:46,583 --> 00:12:48,207
dissenters,

98
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:51,582
who speak together blasphemously...

99
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:52,665
(Whispers)

100
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,749
..tampering with God's work.

101
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:59,207
(Whispering)

102
00:12:59,375 --> 00:13:03,499
Be not drawn by the devil's smile.

103
00:13:03,666 --> 00:13:05,415
(Man whispers) Let go of me.

104
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:06,915
(Pew door bangs)

105
00:13:07,083 --> 00:13:10,124
Now let us... Let us talk of the...

106
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:12,207
Let us now sing hymn...

107
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,249
(Organ plays)

108
00:13:15,416 --> 00:13:17,832
(Congregation stumbles over lyrics)

109
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:21,749
d We go to thee

110
00:13:21,916 --> 00:13:23,040
d To thee...

111
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:25,290
(Another choir sings nearby)

112
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,707
(Choirs drown each other out)

113
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:32,915
(Second choir sings lively song)
d We'll win the day

114
00:13:33,083 --> 00:13:36,957
d Though death and hell obstruct our way

115
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:41,082
d We only need to watch and pray

116
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:45,082
d And then we're sure to win the day

117
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:46,415
(Baby crying)

118
00:13:46,583 --> 00:13:50,249
d Come all and one to glory now

119
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:54,499
d And in this world of sin and woe

120
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:58,790
d Forsake your sins without delay

121
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:02,707
d Believe and you shall win the day

122
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:07,124
d We'll win the day, we'll win the day

123
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:11,332
d Though death and hell obstruct our way

124
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:15,707
d We only need to watch and pray

125
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:20,915
d And then we're sure to win the day

126
00:14:22,125 --> 00:14:23,957
l liked that.

127
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:26,082
And now...

128
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:28,332
we'll pray together.

129
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,540
Give us the vision, Lord,

130
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:40,290
to see past the narrow confines of the field.

131
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:44,457
To the great and infinite glory
of the world beyond.

132
00:14:45,583 --> 00:14:49,707
Help us to stretch ourselves
to the full extent of our being...

133
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:52,874
..that we might be one with all men.

134
00:14:53,958 --> 00:14:56,999
Neither master nor servant

135
00:14:57,166 --> 00:14:59,124
before thine eyes.

136
00:14:59,291 --> 00:15:01,249
Amen.

137
00:15:01,416 --> 00:15:03,499
ALL: Amen.

138
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:09,957
Jesus has given us many blessings.

139
00:15:10,791 --> 00:15:13,082
And one of these, my friends, is the smile.

140
00:15:15,083 --> 00:15:18,582
l lo?e every new day.
But Sunday is the best of all.

141
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:22,124
For how good it is to see all of you
joining here together.

142
00:15:23,041 --> 00:15:24,999
During the coming weeks,

143
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:28,499
we shall be calling upon
the services of my good brother James.

144
00:15:28,666 --> 00:15:30,415
Thank you.

145
00:15:30,583 --> 00:15:32,749
l would like to talk about comradeship,

146
00:15:32,916 --> 00:15:36,832
about the Disciples who laid down their work
to follow in the path of truth.

147
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,499
l look forward to your good attendance.

148
00:15:40,458 --> 00:15:41,874
Praise the Lord.

149
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:43,374
(Girl giggling)

150
00:15:43,541 --> 00:15:45,374
No planning ahead would be complete

151
00:15:45,541 --> 00:15:49,790
without calling upon our good friend
and neighbour Tom Stanfield. Tom.

152
00:15:53,916 --> 00:15:56,374
As well as reading the Word of God,

153
00:15:56,541 --> 00:16:01,165
l shall leave part of my time open for anyone
to approach me with a subject for discussion.

154
00:16:01,333 --> 00:16:05,207
(Whispers)
- All our troubles are shared by Jesus.

155
00:16:05,375 --> 00:16:08,540
So please come forward and don't be shy.

156
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:14,374
lt is worth bearing in mind
a grief shared is a smaller grief.

157
00:16:18,708 --> 00:16:20,832
l see we have a stranger in our midst.

158
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:25,040
l'm glad you had the temerity to enter.

159
00:16:25,208 --> 00:16:28,124
Now we know who trod the grass
these Sundays past.

160
00:16:33,375 --> 00:16:35,457
Welcome, lad.

161
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:38,832
(Organ music)

162
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,082
Good morning. Good morning.

163
00:17:38,583 --> 00:17:40,665
(Men talking nearby)

164
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:46,082
- Hello, John.
- George.

165
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:48,832
What were you doing in church and all?

166
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,082
(Low conversation)

167
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:17,249
(Knocking)

168
00:18:43,041 --> 00:18:44,249
(Latch clicks)

169
00:18:44,416 --> 00:18:46,374
GEORGE: Bridget.

170
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:48,624
BRlDGET: George. Come in.

171
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:53,374
We thought it was the vicar.

172
00:18:54,125 --> 00:18:57,499
l wouldn't trust the vicar with a fart.

173
00:18:57,666 --> 00:19:01,957
Forgive me, my dear chap. l had no idea
we had the pleasure of your company.

174
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:12,332
John.

175
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:15,499
Bridget.

176
00:19:17,250 --> 00:19:19,332
My dear friends.

177
00:19:20,416 --> 00:19:23,290
Your labour is more important
than the Sabbath day?

178
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:31,290
We all need a day of rest.

179
00:19:32,583 --> 00:19:34,790
Maybe your brother has the right idea.

180
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,582
Though it pains me to admit it.

181
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:46,457
l wish times were different, George...

182
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:50,999
..and we could have back
the respect we give to others.

183
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,582
lf you'll forgive me, then, George.

184
00:19:57,791 --> 00:20:00,999
Mr Frampton demands
they be sent in this very week.

185
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,290
They are a work of great beauty.

186
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:10,874
When we create with our hands such harmony,

187
00:20:11,958 --> 00:20:14,040
God is truly present.

188
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:23,332
BRlDGET:
He's been awake the whole night through.

189
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,957
(Light hammering and sanding)

190
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:44,790
Why don't you ask for more payment?

191
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:49,832
Because, George, if they don't like it,
they'll find someone else.

192
00:20:51,125 --> 00:20:53,207
Yes.

193
00:20:59,125 --> 00:21:02,249
But supposing all you carpenters
were to ask for more?

194
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:33,665
(Tapping)

195
00:24:21,375 --> 00:24:23,957
MAN: Arscott.

196
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:29,249
Brown.

197
00:24:33,041 --> 00:24:34,832
Buxton.

198
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:40,249
Sir. Sir, far be it for my friend here
to seek priority over his comrades.

199
00:24:40,416 --> 00:24:41,957
Oh, dear.

200
00:24:42,125 --> 00:24:45,040
Nor do we wish to take yourself
too obviously to task.

201
00:24:45,208 --> 00:24:47,165
But, as l understand the alphabet...

202
00:24:47,333 --> 00:24:54,207
(Mocking posh accent) ..do not the 'l' in 'Brine'
precede the 'O' in 'Brown'?

203
00:24:54,958 --> 00:24:58,415
- And indeed the 'U' in 'Buxton'?
- (Workers chuckling)

204
00:24:58,583 --> 00:25:01,915
ln time...comrade.

205
00:25:02,083 --> 00:25:04,165
- Right.
- ln good time.

206
00:25:07,375 --> 00:25:08,832
MAN: Hammett.

207
00:25:26,833 --> 00:25:28,790
Lost a finger, have you, Hammett?

208
00:25:28,958 --> 00:25:30,915
Or is it just you can't count?

209
00:25:31,083 --> 00:25:32,165
(Chuckling)

210
00:25:33,250 --> 00:25:35,332
Legg!

211
00:25:46,041 --> 00:25:47,999
Loveless!

212
00:25:48,166 --> 00:25:52,249
MAN AT DESK: George first. James following.

213
00:25:52,416 --> 00:25:56,540
Let my brother go first. For l've not reconciled.

214
00:25:56,708 --> 00:25:58,665
Not reconciled what?

215
00:25:58,833 --> 00:26:00,915
My conscience.

216
00:26:03,291 --> 00:26:04,915
Stanfield!

217
00:26:05,083 --> 00:26:07,874
Do you call father or son?

218
00:26:25,791 --> 00:26:27,874
l think there must be some mistake.

219
00:26:28,958 --> 00:26:31,582
We should be getting nine shillings.

220
00:26:32,833 --> 00:26:36,499
- Not eight.
- There's been no mistake, Mr Stanfield.

221
00:26:36,666 --> 00:26:39,374
You must take it or leave it.

222
00:26:48,958 --> 00:26:51,040
Brine!

223
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:55,540
MAN AT DESK: Brine.

224
00:26:58,375 --> 00:27:00,457
Will you sign?

225
00:27:04,291 --> 00:27:06,374
We haven't all day.

226
00:28:31,500 --> 00:28:33,582
(Murmur of distant chatter)

227
00:29:48,291 --> 00:29:50,374
Mother?

228
00:29:57,666 --> 00:29:59,749
l'm hungry.

229
00:30:01,833 --> 00:30:03,915
Let me in.

230
00:30:07,833 --> 00:30:09,915
Mother!

231
00:31:31,583 --> 00:31:33,665
(Sobs)

232
00:31:55,125 --> 00:31:58,957
You mustn't touch. You can look
as much as you like, but don't touch.

233
00:31:59,125 --> 00:32:01,082
- How much are they?
- Ten a penny.

234
00:32:01,250 --> 00:32:04,874
- That isn't a bargain.
- They're a bargain at twice the price.

235
00:32:09,291 --> 00:32:11,249
Wait.

236
00:32:11,416 --> 00:32:13,374
A dozen then, a dozen for a penny.

237
00:32:13,541 --> 00:32:15,624
l only have a half a penny.

238
00:32:15,791 --> 00:32:17,874
l don't really sell ha'penny's worth.

239
00:32:18,041 --> 00:32:19,999
But as a special favour to you,

240
00:32:20,166 --> 00:32:22,374
five for an ha'penny.

241
00:34:03,666 --> 00:34:05,749
Come on, Briney.

242
00:34:18,666 --> 00:34:20,749
Afternoon.

243
00:34:23,083 --> 00:34:25,040
Nice day.

244
00:34:25,208 --> 00:34:27,290
- lnnit?
- lnnit?

245
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:41,374
What are you doing this afternoon, then?

246
00:34:42,250 --> 00:34:43,790
Shall we go blackberry picking?

247
00:34:43,958 --> 00:34:47,499
A bit of blackberry picking in the woods there?
What do you say?

248
00:34:47,666 --> 00:34:50,915
What you do with blackberries,
you squash 'em all up...

249
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:54,082
..you rub them all over your face,

250
00:34:55,166 --> 00:34:57,499
and you lick the juice off.

251
00:34:57,666 --> 00:34:59,749
Be nice?

252
00:35:02,791 --> 00:35:04,874
(They laugh)

253
00:35:05,833 --> 00:35:07,915
Are you all right?

254
00:35:10,375 --> 00:35:12,332
Go off for a walk up the woods, then?

255
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:14,249
(Girl squeals)

256
00:35:14,416 --> 00:35:16,332
Hurry up.

257
00:35:19,750 --> 00:35:21,832
(Whistles)

258
00:35:31,041 --> 00:35:32,999
Hurry up.

259
00:35:33,166 --> 00:35:35,249
Come here.

260
00:35:37,291 --> 00:35:39,374
Here, duck down.

